    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using LSP's foldexp these messages are shown:\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: ...os-x86_64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_capability.lua:174: scoped variable: Invalid buffer id: 13\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function '__newindex'\n\t...os-x86_64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_capability.lua:174: in function 'enable'\n\t...x86_64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_folding_range.lua:347: in function <...x86_64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_folding_range.lua:346>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOn the config enable foldexpr with:\n\n```\no.foldmethod = 'expr'\no.foldexpr = \"v:lua.vim.lsp.foldexpr()\"\n```\n\nThen navigate on any buffer that has LSP enabled.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo ignore invalid buffers on the foldexpr function and no message to be shown.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1065+g c1fa3c7c37\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 11.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly build from repo",
